# Walkthrough: Fixing Compilation Errors and Running GridWorld Programs

I fixed the errors in the [BoxBug](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/School/10th-grade/APCSA/GridWorld/src/GridWorldCode/projects/boxBug/BoxBug.java#25-58) compilation and started the [CircleBug](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/School/10th-grade/APCSA/GridWorld/src/GridWorldCode/projects/boxBug/CircleBugRunner.java#30-43) program as requested.

## Changes Made

### 1. Identified Syntax Errors
The common errors when moving from Windows to Mac (or Linux) are:
- **Quotes**: Using "curly quotes" (`“`, `”`) instead of standard straight quotes (`"`).
- **Classpath Separator**: Windows uses `;`, while Mac uses `:`.
- **Package Paths**: Running classes requires pointing to the root of the source directory.

### 2. Compiled and Ran BoxBug
The correct commands for your Mac environment are:
```bash
# Compile from project root
javac -cp "src/GridWorldCode/gridworld.jar" src/GridWorldCode/projects/boxBug/*.java

# Run from project root (note the : instead of ;)
java -cp "src:src/GridWorldCode/gridworld.jar" GridWorldCode.projects.boxBug.BoxBugRunner
```

### 4. Increased Grid Size
I updated [CircleBugRunner.java](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/School/10th-grade/APCSA/GridWorld/src/GridWorldCode/projects/boxBug/CircleBugRunner.java) to use a **20x20 BoundedGrid**. This was done by:
- Importing `info.gridworld.actor.Actor` and `info.gridworld.grid.BoundedGrid`.
- Changing the `ActorWorld` constructor to `new ActorWorld(new BoundedGrid<Actor>(20, 20))`.

